observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Require the GSO-Designate to strictly comply with the required physical count of all properties at least once a year using the proper format and to submit a copy of the said reports to the Audit Team not later than January 31 of every year;

Require the GSO-Designate to maintain complete Property Cards for the PPEs of the LGU;

Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain  Property Ledger Cards and be reconciled with the Property Cards of the GSO-Designate;

Require the GSO-Designate to adopt a uniform property identification system for PPE wherein a unique Property Number shall be assigned for each item and on which the Property Number shall be prominently shown in the property sticker, showing all the vital information of the PPE to facilitate a methodological system of inventory-taking and to strengthen internal control on PPE; and

Monitor closely the implementation of Executive Order No. 03, series of 2022 re: Reorganizing the Inventory and Disposal Committee of the LGU to spearhead the conduct of the One-Time Cleansing of PPEs pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020.

\We have recommended that Local Chief Executive undertake the following courses of action:

Require the Municipal Engineer to spearhead the physical inventory of the road networks because of his technical knowledge and skills in engineering;

Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;

Require the General Services Officer or its equivalent to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map, and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components using the format prescribed under COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network using the prescribed format as mentioned in the above circular.

We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive undertake the following courses of action, to wit:

Verify the validity of Accounts Payable aged two years or more;

Send confirmation letters for balances with identified claimants or creditors;  

Revert any payables to the unappropriated surplus of the General Fund when these are found to have no valid supporting documents.

