We have recommended management the following:
Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network using the prescribed format as mentioned in the above circular and disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the total road network system;
For the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
For the General Services Officer to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map, and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components also using the prescribed format as mentioned in the above circular;
Create an inventory committee to conduct the physical count and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System.

We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive to:
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to prepare the duly certified list of taxpayers showing the names and the amount due and collectible based on RPTAR/Taxpayer’s index card or computer-generated report prepared by the Municipal Treasurer in coordination with the Municipal Assessor and;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to base the setting up of RPT and SET Receivable at the beginning of the year from the duly certified list of taxpayers prepared by the Municipal Treasury Office which is more accurate and reliable in order to fairly present the accounts in the financial statements.

We have recommended that the local government unit strictly adhere with the existing laws, rules and regulations covering the appropriation and utilization of the 20% Local Development Fund to avoid possible sanctions that may be imposed for non-compliance. Further, we have recommended the following:

That the 20% Local Development Fund be optimally utilize in order to deliver the benefits of desirable social, economic and environmental outcomes to the constituents which is essential in the attainment of the constitutional objective of a desired quality of life for all;

That that the Local Chief Executive ensure the 20% Local Development Fund is utilized within the purposes expressly prescribed by law to ensure that funds for programs/projects/activities geared toward the welfare of its constituents would not be sacrificed.

