Recommendation/s:

In view of the foregoing deficiencies, we have recommended that –

a)	The concerned officials and employees submit the supporting documents being required for further evaluation of the COA ROI Technical Evaluation Services and Audit Team and in order to avoid suspension in audit; 

b)	The Local Chief Executive require the supplier of one (1) unit generator set and two (2) units trailing plow harrow to pay the unliquidated damages in the amount of  P117,406.00 and P32,922.00, respectively, in view of delay in the delivery;

c)	Brand name be specified in the bid proposal and purchase order to serve as basis of the Bids and Awards Committee in the evaluation of the quality of goods to be procured and to avoid legal problems in the future; and 

d)	The Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer ensure the completeness of supporting documents before affixing their signatures in the disbursement vouchers and before effecting payment of transactions related to the concerned procurement.

Recommendation/s:

We have recommended that the Municipal Treasurer strictly comply with the provisions of existing laws, rules and regulations in the proper handling, custody and disposition of cash and recording of cash transactions to safeguard the government funds from risk of loss, theft or misuse. For the foregoing deficiencies, we have recommended the following:
a. 	The Local Chief Executive require the Municipal Treasurer to deposit intact her collections with the authorized government depository bank daily or not later than the next banking day;

b. 	The Municipal Treasurer utilize only regular and bonded revenue collectors to undertake the collection; 

c. 	Ruling, closing and certification be made on the cashbook at the end of each month to ascertain the accuracy and reliability of the balances; 

d. 	The accountable forms be issued in strict numerical sequence; and

e. 	Refrain from accommodating private checks using government funds.

We have reiterated our previous year’s recommendation that the local government unit ensure management and accounting of its properties by observing the procedures provided by existing rules and regulations in the custody and management of properties specifically:

Keeping of Property Cards per category of Property, Plant and Equipment by the General Services Officer, Supply Officer or the Local Treasurer, as the case maybe;
Maintaining Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards for each category of assets and Real Property Ledger Cards for land by the Municipal Accountant;
Conducting annual physical inventory of all supplies or property of the local government unit as of December 31 of each year and submission of the report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) to the auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year;
Reconciling the balance of the Property, Plant and Equipment with property card, ledger cards and RPCPPE; and
Making use of Inventory Custodian Slips for control and monitoring of semi-expendable items to avoid loss, as these are usually small items.

In view of the foregoing, we have recommended that the Bids and Awards Committee, who has the responsibility for ensuring that the procuring entity abides by the standards set forth by RA 9184 and its IRR, strictly adhere with all provisions of laws, rules and regulations pertaining to procurements to protect at all times the interest of the local government unit. For the foregoing deficiencies noted, we have recommended that –
Observers from a duly recognized private group in a sector or discipline relevant to the procurement at hand be invited in all stages of the procurement;
The Notices of Award and Notices to proceed and the approved contract of projects awarded be posted in the agency website of the procuring entity and any conspicuous place within the premises;
Final APP be submitted in the GPPB on or before the end of January of the budget year and posted in the GPPB website;
Standard rates provided under Section 5 of Annex A of GPPB Resolution No. 04-2012 be strictly observed in the sale of bid documents; and
Required documents be submitted to avoid suspension in audit.

